- now all the new changes are gone. This definitely means that we need more understanding in dealing with GitHub.

reminder:

1. Always pull before pushing - Make sure your local branch is up-to-date with the remote before pushing
2. Use feature branches - Create separate branches for different changes rather than pushing directly to main
3. Review before pushing - Use git status and git diff to verify what you're about to push
4. Git history is recoverable - Your changes might still be in the Git reflog or commit history if they were committed

